---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About | VTech App"
	description="VTech App is an independent free software provider focused on useful system utilities for real-world users and administrators."
>
	<header class="page-heading">
		<p class="eyebrow">About VTech App</p>
		<h1>Independent free software for practical system work.</h1>
		<p>
			VTech App builds focused utilities for Windows users, technicians, and system
			administrators who need clear tools for real operational tasks.
		</p>
		<a class="button" href="mailto:vtechinf1@gmail.com">Contact vtechinf1@gmail.com</a>
	</header>

	<section class="feature-grid">
		<article class="card">
			<h2>What VTech App builds</h2>
			<p>
				Utilities for storage visibility, permission-safe file operations, file-server auditing,
				and other workflows where small focused tools can save time.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Why these tools exist</h2>
			<p>
				System work often depends on clear information and predictable operations. VTech App is
				designed around practical needs rather than account systems or hosted dashboards.
			</p>
		</article>
		<article class="card">
			<h2>Development philosophy</h2>
			<p>
				Keep utilities focused, honest about release status, easy to understand, and useful for
				technicians and administrators doing real work.
			</p>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="roadmap-grid">
		<article class="card roadmap-card">
			<p class="eyebrow">Current platform</p>
			<h2>Windows utilities</h2>
			<p>
				Windows is the active development focus because many storage, permissions, migration,
				and file-server workflows happen there.
			</p>
			<a class="button" href="/apps/">View Windows apps</a>
		</article>
		<article class="card roadmap-card">
			<p class="eyebrow">Available platform</p>
			<h2>Linux utilities</h2>
			<p>
				The first Linux utility is live now. More Linux tools are planned for future releases.
			</p>
			<a class="button" href="/apps/#linux">Browse Linux apps</a>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="notice">
		<h2>Project goal</h2>
		<p>
			The goal is to build software that solves practical problems without unnecessary accounts,
			lock-in, fake download states, or paid-service dependencies.
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>
